# Memories: Photo Management for Nextcloud

Memories is a *batteries-included* photo management solution for Nextcloud with advanced features including:

- **üì∏ Timeline**: Sort photos and videos by date taken, parsed from Exif data.
- **‚è™ Rewind**: Jump to any time in the past instantly and relive your memories.
- **ü§ñ AI Tagging**: Group photos by people and objects, powered by [recognize](https://github.com/nextcloud/recognize) and [facerecognition](https://github.com/matiasdelellis/facerecognition).
- **üñºÔ∏è Albums**: Create albums to group photos and videos together. Then share these albums with others.
- **ü´±üèª‚Äçü´≤üèª External Sharing**: Share photos and videos with people outside of your Nextcloud instance.
- **üì± Mobile Support**: Work from any device, of any shape and size through the web app.
- **‚úèÔ∏è Edit Metadata**: Edit dates and other metadata on photos quickly and in bulk.
- **üì¶ Archive**: Store photos you don't want to see in your timeline in a separate folder.
- **üìπ Video Transcoding**: Transcode videos and use HLS for maximal performance.
- **üó∫Ô∏è Map**: View your photos on a map, tagged with accurate reverse geocoding.
- **üì¶ Migration**: Migrate easily from Nextcloud Photos and Google Takeout.
- **‚ö°Ô∏è Performance**: Do all this very fast.

## üöÄ Installation

1. Install the app from the Nextcloud app store (try a demo [here](https://demo.memories.gallery/apps/memories/)).
1. Perform the recommended [configuration steps](https://memories.gallery/config/).
1. Run `php occ memories:index` to generate metadata indices for existing photos.
1. Open the üì∑ Memories app in Nextcloud and set the directory containing your photos.
